---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'July 7, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Voq"
  description="Voq's privacy policy: the Chrome extension reads webpage text aloud using your browser's built-in Web Speech API and does not collect, store, or transmit any user data."
>
  <div class="container">
    <article class="prose">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        Voq is a free Chrome extension that reads webpage text aloud. This
        page explains what data Voq does — and does not — handle.
      </p>

      <h2>Summary</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Voq does not collect any personal data.</li>
        <li>Voq does not store any user data, on your device or on a server.</li>
        <li>Voq does not require an account or sign-up.</li>
        <li>Voq has no analytics, tracking, or advertising of any kind.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How Voq works</h2>
      <p>
        When you select text on a webpage and choose to have it read aloud,
        Voq passes that text directly to your browser's built-in
        <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Speech_API" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Web Speech API</a>,
        which converts it to speech on your device. The text is not sent to
        Voq's servers, because Voq does not operate any servers that process
        or store webpage content.
      </p>

      <h2>Data collection</h2>
      <p>
        Voq does not collect, store, or transmit any of the following:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The text or webpages you have Voq read aloud</li>
        <li>Your browsing history</li>
        <li>Personal information, such as your name, email, or IP address</li>
        <li>Usage analytics or telemetry</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Voq does not use cookies, does not include any third-party trackers,
        and does not share data with any third party, because no data is
        collected in the first place.
      </p>

      <h2>Permissions</h2>
      <p>
        Voq requests only the browser permissions it needs to read the
        current page's text aloud and display its reading controls. These
        permissions are used solely to provide that functionality on your
        device and are never used to collect or transmit data elsewhere.
      </p>

      <h2>Accounts</h2>
      <p>
        Voq does not require you to create an account or sign in. You can
        install and use Voq immediately after adding it to Chrome.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Voq does not knowingly collect any data from anyone, including
        children, because it does not collect data at all.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If this privacy policy ever changes, the updated version will be
        posted on this page with a revised "Last updated" date.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this privacy policy, you can reach out
        via the contact information listed on Voq's Chrome Web Store
        listing.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>
